                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C1199/218a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-26T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. Please deliver the following message to Stoppani from Rogers: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I am designating Mr. Leo Pasvolsky<note n="8a" xml:id="d370fn8a"
                                >Economic Analyst in the Department of State.</note> as alternate to
                            myself for the next meeting of the Economic Committee. We will both be
                            in attendance. I understand and trust this is agreeable to you and to
                            the Committee.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
